---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const pageTitle = "Work";
const description = "Resumé of Michael P. LeRoux";
---

<BaseLayout pageTitle={pageTitle} description={description}>
  <section class="mb-20">
    <h1>{pageTitle}</h1>

    <p class="mb-10">
      I'm currently available for contract or permanent work in the Boston area.
      I'd <a href="mailto:&#109;&#105;&#099;&#104;&#097;&#101;&#108;&#046;&#108;&#101;&#114;&#111;&#117;&#120;&#064;&#103;&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#109;">love to talk</a> if you think
      my experience would be a good fit.
    </p>
    <hr class="mb-10" />

    <h2 class="mb-2">Michael P. LeRoux</h2>

    <p class="mb-0">
      Somerville, MA • <a
        href="mailto:&#109;&#105;&#099;&#104;&#097;&#101;&#108;&#046;&#108;&#101;&#114;&#111;&#117;&#120;&#064;&#103;&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#046;&#099;&#111;&#109;"
        aria-label="Email"
        target="_blank">Email</a
      >
    </p>
    <p class="mb-4">
      LinkedIn: <a
        href="https://linkedin.com/in/michaelleroux"
        aria-label="LinkedIn"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        target="_blank">linkedin.com/in/michaelleroux</a
      > • GitHub: <a
        href="https://github.com/mpleroux"
        aria-label="GitHub"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        target="_blank"
        >github.com/mpleroux
      </a>
    </p>

    <h3 class="pt-3">SUMMARY</h3>

    <p>
      <span class="font-medium">Web Developer</span> with a strong focus on building
      polished, consistent user interfaces. Proven track record of collaborating with
      cross-functional teams to streamline content workflows and bridge technical
      gaps. Dedicated to maintainable code, clear documentation, and contributing
      to a collaborative engineering culture. Currently leveraging a professional
      background in <span class="font-medium">JavaScript</span> and <span
        class="font-medium">TypeScript</span
      > to expand my toolkit with <span class="font-medium">React</span>, <span
        class="font-medium">Next.js</span
      >, <span class="font-medium">Astro</span>, and AI-assisted tools like <span
        class="font-medium">Claude Code</span
      > and
      <span class="font-medium">Gemini</span>.
    </p>

    <h3 class="pt-3">TECHNICAL SKILLS</h3>

    <ul>
      <li>
        <b>Core Proficiencies:</b> JavaScript (ES6+), TypeScript, Vue.js, Nuxt, Tailwind
        CSS, HTML5, CSS3/SCSS, Python, Django
      </li>
      <li>
        <b>Platform & Infrastructure:</b> Storyblok CMS, PrimeVue, AWS, REST APIs,
        Git/GitHub
      </li>
      <li>
        <b>Development Standards:</b> Responsive Design, Web Accessibility (a11y),
        Technical Documentation, Component-Driven Architecture
      </li>
      <li>
        <b>Current Focus & Implementation:</b> React, Next.js, Astro, Claude Code,
        Gemini
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="pt-3">PROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE</h3>

    <h4 class="mb-0">
      Senior Software Engineer &ndash; EnergySage &ndash; Boston, MA
    </h4>
    <p class="mb-1"><i>October 2012 &ndash; June 2025</i></p>

    <ul>
      <li>
        Architected and maintained scalable Vue.js components using
        <span class="font-medium">JavaScript/TypeScript</span> and an internal design
        system, improving UI consistency and developer efficiency.
      </li>
      <li>
        Integrated <span class="font-medium">Storyblok</span> CMS to empower non-technical
        stakeholders to independently update content, significantly reducing engineering
        support requests.
      </li>
      <li>
        Standardized styling across legacy and modern codebases by consolidating
        <span class="font-medium">Bootstrap</span> and <span class="font-medium"
          >CSS</span
        > patterns, reducing UI drift and simplifying maintenance.
      </li>
      <li>
        Authored technical documentation for architectural decisions and
        frontend services to streamline onboarding and cross-team knowledge
        sharing.
      </li>
      <li>
        Mentored junior developers through code reviews and pair programming,
        accelerating their progression to independent contributors.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h4 class="mb-0">Web Developer &ndash; Verndale &ndash; Boston, MA</h4>
    <p class="mb-1"><i>April 2012 &ndash; October 2012</i></p>

    <ul>
      <li>
        Developed responsive, accessible website templates from design comps and
        interaction specs.
      </li>
      <li>
        Collaborated with QA to ensure cross-browser compatibility and reliable
        user experiences.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="pt-3">EDUCATION</h3>

    <h4>
      Bachelor of Science, Computer Science &ndash; University of Massachusetts
      Dartmouth
    </h4>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
